Source: The Guardian, "Russia and Ukraine confirm three-day ceasefire from 9 May". Published Fri 8 May 2026 21.07 EDT, first published 14.23 EDT. Captured text includes headline and article body stating: "Both sides also confirm prisoner swap which Donald Trump announced along with suspension of all 'kinetic activity' between the warring states." The article reports that Donald Trump announced a three-day ceasefire in the war between Russia and Ukraine from 9 to 11 May. It states that the US president said the ceasefire would include a suspension of all "kinetic activity" and a swap of 1,000 prisoners from each country, and that it was confirmed by both sides. The article reports that Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy confirmed Trump's announcement and the prisoner swap on Friday night, writing on Telegram: "We received Russia's agreement to conduct a prisoner exchange in the format of 1,000 for 1,000. A ceasefire regime must also be established on May 9, 10, and 11." It further reports Zelenskyy wrote that Red Square was less important than the lives of Ukrainian prisoners and that Ukraine expected the United States to ensure Russia fulfilled the agreements. The article reports Russia confirmed the truce and POW swap, quoting Kremlin foreign policy adviser Yuri Ushakov: "I confirm the acceptability for the Russian side of the initiative just proposed by US president Donald Trump, concerning a ceasefire for a prisoner-of-war exchange between Russia and Ukraine." The article also notes both sides had accused each other of violating previous ceasefires.